	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - Firefighters are still trying to extinguish a fire which destroyed about seven informal dwellings in Lamontville, Durban, in the early hours of Monday morning, KwaZulu-Natal Emergency Medical Services said. The fire began around 05:00, spokesperson Robert Mckenzie told News24. One person was being treated on the scene. It was not immediately clear whether there had been any fatalities. "We don't have a fatality count because the guys are still fighting the fire," Mckenzie said. More details to follow. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  